## Transcript System (v4.3)

### JSONL-Based Transcripts

Claude Code stores conversations in JSONL format at `~/.claude/projects/[encoded-path]/[session-id].jsonl`. The transcript system reads this directly instead of capturing terminal output.

**Benefits over terminal capture:**
- Clean structured data (no ANSI cleaning)
- Accurate timestamps per message
- Tool calls properly formatted
- No terminal UI artifacts

### Two Modes

| Command | Mode | Use Case |
|---------|------|----------|
| `./pipeline transcript` | Post-session | Analysis, archiving |
| `./pipeline stream` | Live | Frontend, real-time monitoring |

### Commands

```bash
# List sessions for a project
./pipeline sessions /home/claude/IMT/my-project

# Generate transcript from latest session (post-session)
./pipeline transcript /home/claude/IMT/my-project

# Generate transcript with tool calls
./pipeline transcript /home/claude/IMT/my-project --tools

# Generate from specific session
./pipeline transcript /home/claude/IMT/my-project --session <uuid>

# Live stream (JSON format - best for frontend)
./pipeline stream /home/claude/IMT/my-project --format json

# Live stream (markdown format)
./pipeline stream /home/claude/IMT/my-project --format markdown

# Live stream with tool calls
./pipeline stream /home/claude/IMT/my-project --format json --tools
```

### Stream Output Formats

**JSON** (default - best for frontend parsing):
```json
{"type":"user","timestamp":"2025-11-25T09:01:07Z","content":"analyze the system"}
{"type":"assistant","content":"I'll analyze the system..."}
{"type":"tool","name":"Read"}
```

**Markdown** (for display):
